    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="294" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Eustis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 8,
                                        1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 539.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that
                                your dispatch, No. 381, of the 27th ultimo, relative to the arrival
                                of Mrs. John L. Waller and her family in France and the expenses
                                incurred by you on account of sending them to the United States, has
                                been received.</p>
                <p>Your course in regard to the matter is fully approved by the
                                Department, and you are hereby authorized to draw on the Secretary
                                of State for the aggregate amount of the expenses incurred by you in
                                the premises, supporting your draft by an itemized account with
                                vouchers in the usual manner.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard
                                Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
